Durban - A man and a woman were killed in two separate train incidents in KwaZulu-Natal over the weekend. An elderly man was killed on the Etete railway crossing, north of Durban, on Saturday morning. Paul Herbst of IPSS Medical Rescue said a vehicle crossing a railway line was knocked by a goods train. “The light motor vehicle belonging to and driven by an elderly Indian male, was dragged for approximately 60m before the train come to a stop,” Herbst said. He said the man was declared dead on arrival by IPSS paramedics. Earlier, a pregnant woman was knocked and killed by a train next to Camperdown informal settlement in Camperdown, northwest of Durban. Russel Meiring, ER24 spokesperson, said ER24 paramedics responded to the scene of the incident and were escorted along the tracks to where they found the woman. “Upon assessment, paramedics found that the woman had sustained numerous injuries and showed no signs of life. Unfortunately, nothing could be done for her and she was declared dead,” Meiring said. He said no one was injured from the goods train and the cause of the incident is unknown but police were on scene investigating. Daily News